quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  18,45,"And give them a parable of this worldly life. ňĻIt isňļ like the plants of the earth, thriving when sustained by the rain We send down from the sky. Then they ňĻsoonňļ turn into chaff scattered by the wind. And God is fully capable of ňĻdoingňļ all things"
  18,46,"Wealth and children are the adornment of this worldly life, but the everlasting good deeds are far better with your Lord in reward and in hope"
  18,47,"ňĻBeware ofňļ the Day We will blow the mountains away, and you will see the earth laid bare. And We will gather all ňĻhumankindňļ, leaving none behind"
  18,48,"They will be presented before your Lord in rows, ňĻand the deniers will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúYou have surely returned to Us ňĻall aloneňļ as We created you the first time, although you ňĻalwaysňļ claimed that We would never appoint a time for your return.‚ÄĚ"
  18,49,"And the record ňĻof deedsňļ will be laid ňĻopenňļ, and you will see the wicked in fear of what is ňĻwrittenňļ in it. They will cry, ‚ÄúWoe to us! What kind of record is this that does not leave any sin, small or large, unlisted?‚ÄĚ They will find whatever they did present ňĻbefore themňļ. And your Lord will never wrong anyone"